.so ../bk-macros
.TH "bk" 1 %E% "\*(BC" "\*(UM"
.SH NAME
bk bk \- \*(BK source management system front end
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bk 
.ARG command 
.Bc [
.ARGc options
.B ]
.br
.B bk \-R
.ARG command 
.Bc [
.ARGc options
.B ]
.br
.Bc bk [
.OPTopt \-r dir
.B ]
.ARG command
.Bc [
.ARG options
.B ]
.br
.B bk [\-sfiles_opts] 
.OPTopt \-r dir
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B bk
is the front end to all \*(BK commands.
All \*(BK commands are prefixed with 
.B bk
in order to avoid ambiguity with
non-\*(BK commands that might be on the system such as 
.B get
and
.BR ci .
.LP
If you are looking for instructions on how to get started, try running the
test drive at \f(CWhttp://www.bitkeeper.com/Test.html\fP.
.SH OPTIONS
.if t .TP
.if n .TP 1i
.B \-R
Change directories to the root of the repository before running the command.
.tp
.OPTopt \-r dir
Starting at 
.ARG dir ,
or the repository root if 
.ARG dir
was not specified, apply the command recursively to
.ARG dir
and all subdirectories.  This works by
generating a list of sfiles and passing them to the command.  
.tp
.B \-sfiles_opts
Used as a shortcut for sfiles.  The following sfiles options may be passed:
.RS 1i
.TP
.B \-1
Only examine one directory level.  Do not go into subdirectories.
.tp
.B \-a
examine all files, even if listed in BitKeeper/etc/ignore.
.tp
.B \-c
List changed files (locked and modified).
.tp
.B \-d
List directories under \*(BK control (SCCS subdir exists).
.tp
.B \-D
List directories with no (or empty) SCCS subdirs.
.tp
.B \-e
shorthand for
.B \-dDGjluvx
.tp
.B \-E
shorthand for
.B \-cdDGjlnuvxp
.tp
.B \-g
List the gfile name, not the sfile name.
.tp
.B \-G
List files if and only if they are checked out ("gotten").
.tp
.B \-j
List junk files, i.e., files in \*(SC subdirectories which are not
metadata.
.tp
.B \-l
List locked files (p.file and/or z.file).
.tp
.B \-n
list s.files that are not in the correct location.
.tp
.B \-p
list files with pending deltas.  
.tp
.B \-S
produce a summary listing only, typically combined with -E.
.tp
.B \-u
List unlocked files.
.tp
.B \-U
list user files only, skipping all files in the
.B BitKeeper/
subdirectory as well as the
.B ChangeSet
file.
.tp
.B \-x
List files which have no revision control files.
.RE
.SH NOTE
.LP
The following commands are equivalent:
.if n .sp -1
.DS
bk -r get
bk -R sfiles | bk -R get -
cd `bk root`; bk sfiles | bk get -
.DE
.SH "SEE ALSO"
.SA sfiles 1
.SH CATEGORY
.B Repository
